  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "The questionnaire survey approach has been widely acknowledged as a useful method for obtaining information that is challenging to acquire using observational methods, as reported in various studies (Khan et al. 2017).",
    "To ensure the reliability and consistency of our survey instrument, we conducted a pilot evaluation following the questionnaire's design.",
    "Pre-testing the survey, as highlighted in prior research, is crucial for improving the questionnaire's quality and obtaining pertinent responses from the target population (Khan et al. 2021; Failed 2023b).",
    "For the pilot testing, we invited ten experts, including six from the initial unstructured interviews and four new participants.",
    "These experts represented institutions such as King Saud University in Saudi Arabia, the University of Oulu Finland, Nanjing University in China, and Aligarh Muslim University in India."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "The questionnaire survey approach has been widely acknowledged as a useful method for obtaining information that is challenging to acquire using observational methods, as reported in various studies (Khan et al. 2017).",
    "Pre-testing the survey, as highlighted in prior research, is crucial for improving the questionnaire's quality and obtaining pertinent responses from the target population (Khan et al. 2021; Failed 2023b)."
  ]
